### C language specifics

~ Should
provide both dynamic and static linking options for your library.  Each has its own merits and use cases.
~

~ Must
publish your package in source code format.  Due to differences in platforms, this is the most common publishing mechanism for C libraries.
~

~ Must
publish your package to [vcpkg](https://github.com/Microsoft/vcpkg), a C++ library manager supporting Windows, Linux, and MacOS.
~

~ Should
publish libraries targeted to Linux to standard Linux package managers
~

